
When his monthly pension of $6,500 was slashed by 73 percent two weeks ago, retired Delta Air Lines pilot Wendell Lewis decided to make a statement. He put his pilot's uniform up for sale on eBay with a starting bid of $1 &mdash; along with a heartfelt description of what the suit had been through before the Boeing 777 captain retired last December. "Suit comes with a promise of a pension if you provide years of dedication and service," wrote Lewis, of Duluth. "THE PROMISE MAY BE AS EMPTY AS THE SUIT." 

